fields.title: Kenya
fields.body:
Kenya is located on Africa's East Coast, across from the equator. To the north, it shares borders with Somalia, Ethiopia, and Sudan. To the west, Tanzania, Uganda, and east, the Indian Ocean. The country is roughly the size of Texas State, United States, with 225 000 square miles (582 646 square kilometers).

Geography and Climate

The central highlands rise from the Indian Ocean shore. The highlands are divided by the Great Rift Valley. East of the city is a rich plateau. One of Africa's most fruitful agricultural regions is the highlands. At 17,057 feet, Mount Kenya is the second-highest mountain in Africa.

On the coast, Kenya has a tropical climate, although the interior of the country is dry. It rains a lot between March and May. Although there is little rain in October and November, temperatures are still high.

Kenya experiences a lot of sunshine all year long. Both at night and in the morning, it is cool. The prolonged rainy season lasts from April through June. October through December make up the brief. Below is a map of Kenya.
